The paper deals with the classification of binary systematic codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the weight distribution of the codes, which is a topic related to cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper may also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI) as error-correcting codes are used in these fields.
